1 Carga de packages y datos

Code 
# Carga de paquetes necesarios
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(wordcloud)
library(tidytext)
library(textdata)
library(stopwords)
library(DT)
library(here)
library(factoextra)
library(pastecs)
library(psych)

# Carga de los datos
songs <- read_tsv(here("data", "songs.tsv"))
lyrics <- read_tsv(here("data", "lyrics.tsv"))

songs_unique <- songs %>%
  distinct(track_name, .keep_all = TRUE)

lyrics_unique <- lyrics %>%
  distinct(song_name, .keep_all = TRUE)

# Realizar el join despuÃ©s de eliminar duplicados
data <- songs_unique %>%
  mutate(track_name = str_to_lower(track_name)) %>%
  inner_join(
    lyrics_unique %>% mutate(song_name = str_to_lower(song_name)),
    by = c("track_name" = "song_name")
  )

3 AnÃ¡lisis textual

3.1 Frecuencia de palabras

Code 
# Obtener las stopwords en espaÃ±ol
stopwords_es <- stopwords("es")

# Limpieza de texto y tokenizaciÃ³n
tokens <- data %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, lyrics) %>%
  anti_join(tibble(word = stopwords_es), by = "word") %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE)

# VisualizaciÃ³n de las palabras mÃ¡s frecuentes
tokens %>%
  top_n(20) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(word, n), y = n)) +
  geom_col(fill = "purple") +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(
    title = "Palabras mÃ¡s frecuentes en las letras",
    x = "Palabras",
    y = "Frecuencia"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

3.2 Nube de palabras

Code 
# Generar una nube de palabras
set.seed(123)
wordcloud::wordcloud(
  words = tokens$word,
  freq = tokens$n,
  max.words = 100,
  colors = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")
)
